prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "The system checks if everything is working when powered on.",
      "evidence_quote": "The system starts when the power is turned on and checks if everything is working."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "If there is a problem during startup, the system stops.",
      "evidence_quote": "If there is a problem, it stops."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "If everything is fine during startup, the system becomes ready to use.",
      "evidence_quote": "If everything is fine, it becomes ready to use."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "When the system is ready to use, the user can reset it.",
      "evidence_quote": "When it is ready to use, the user can reset it, activate it, or turn it off."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "When the system is ready to use, the user can activate it.",
      "evidence_quote": "When it is ready to use, the user can reset it, activate it, or turn it off."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "When the system is ready to use, the user can turn it off.",
      "evidence_quote": "When it is ready to use, the user can reset it, activate it, or turn it off."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "If the system is activated, it starts monitoring.",
      "evidence_quote": "If activated, the system starts monitoring."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "If a sensor is triggered while monitoring, the alarm starts and alerts are sent.",
      "evidence_quote": "If a sensor is triggered, the alarm starts and alerts are sent."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "If it turns out to be a false alarm or the time ends, the system continues monitoring.",
      "evidence_quote": "If it turns out to be a false alarm or the time ends, it continues monitoring."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "At any time, the user can enter the password to stop the system and bring it back to normal.",
      "evidence_quote": "At any time, the user can enter the password to stop it and bring it back to normal."
    }
  ]
}

